Event.description: When the video emerged of a Minneapolis policeman

metatags.apple-mobile-web-app-title: Why aren’t mainstream Israelis and American Jews supporting Palestinians? | Middle East Institute
metatags.og:description: When the video emerged of a Minneapolis policeman pressing his knee on the neck of George Floyd as he lay on the ground, Palestinians were surprised by the image — the technique was all too familiar. But while hundreds of thousands of people have taken to the streets to protest the killing of George Floyd, an African-American male, by police across the U.S. and around the world, the response among Israelis and American Jews to violence against Palestinians is quite different. Many liberal Jewish leaders and thinkers who have spoken out forcefully against the killing of Floyd are silent when it comes to the atrocities committed by Israeli soldiers.
metatags.twitter:image:alt: Photo by AHMAD GHARABLI/AFP via Getty Images
